name: LG4M
notes: LG4M has gamma rates by design. Thus, it doesn't make much sense to use it without them.

name: LG4X
notes: LG4X has 4 free rate categories by design, so it doesn't make sense to use it without a rate distribution.

name: GTR
notes: Not possible, because by definition the GTR model does not have any amino acid frequencies with it. So they either need to be estimated from the data empirically (see GTR+F) or by ML (not implemented in RAxML or, therefore, PartitionFinder).

name: LG4M+F
notes: Advised against in the RAxML v8 Manual, so not impelemented in PF

name: GTR+X
